# Email Service Configuration Template
# Copy this to .env.local and fill in your credentials

# ========================================
# OPTION 1: SendGrid Configuration
# ========================================
# Get these from https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/api_keys

# Your SendGrid API key
SENDGRID_API_KEY=

# Verified sender email address
SENDGRID_FROM_EMAIL=hello@hive.college

# Optional: Dynamic template ID for custom email design
# Create at https://mc.sendgrid.com/dynamic-templates
SENDGRID_MAGIC_LINK_TEMPLATE_ID=

# ========================================
# OPTION 2: Firebase Email Configuration
# ========================================
# Configure in Firebase Console:
# https://console.firebase.google.com/project/[YOUR_PROJECT]/authentication/providers
#
# 1. Enable Email/Password provider
# 2. Enable Email link (passwordless sign-in)
# 3. Customize email templates under Templates tab
#
# Firebase automatically handles email delivery when configured

# ========================================
# Testing Email Delivery
# ========================================
# 1. In development, emails will log to console if not configured
# 2. Use test email domains for development:
#    - @test.edu for development mode
#    - @buffalo.edu for production testing

# ========================================
# Production Checklist
# ========================================
# [ ] SendGrid account verified and active
# [ ] Sender domain authenticated in SendGrid
# [ ] From email address verified
# [ ] SPF/DKIM records configured for domain
# [ ] Email templates tested
# [ ] Rate limits configured appropriately
# [ ] Bounce/complaint handling set up

# ========================================
# Email Provider Comparison
# ========================================
# SendGrid:
# - Pros: Better deliverability, detailed analytics, custom templates
# - Cons: Requires paid plan for volume, more setup
# - Best for: Production with high volume
#
# Firebase Email:
# - Pros: Free tier generous, integrated with auth, simple setup
# - Cons: Basic templates, less control, limited analytics
# - Best for: MVP and early stage